// Get variables from Configurations
var gcpProject = kaholo.execution.configuration.gcpProject
var gcpProjectNumber = kaholo.execution.configuration.gcpProjectNumber
var region = kaholo.execution.configuration.region
var zone = kaholo.execution.configuration.zone
var genericTag = kaholo.execution.configuration.genericTag
var vpcName = kaholo.execution.configuration.vpcName
var subnetCidr = kaholo.execution.configuration.subnetCidr
var wpImageProject = kaholo.execution.configuration.wpImageProject
var wpImageName = kaholo.execution.configuration.wpImageName
var machineName = kaholo.execution.configuration.machineName
var machineType = kaholo.execution.configuration.machineType
var slackChannel = kaholo.execution.configuration.slackChannel

// Hard code variables or variables calculated from other variables
var serviceAccount = gcpProjectNumber+"-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com"
var sshIngress = "35.235.240.0/20"
var sshRule = "allow-ssh"
var httpRule = "allow-http"
var httpsRule = "allow-https"
var wpImageUrl = "https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/"+wpImageProject+"/global/images/"+wpImageName
var vpcUrl = "https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/"+gcpProject+"/global/networks/"+vpcName
var subnetName = vpcName+"-"+region
var subnetUrl = "https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/"+gcpProject+"/regions/"+region+"/subnetworks/"+subnetName

processes.name: create-vpc
processes.description: Creates a new VPC to host your Wordpress Compute instances - ensures network separation from other GCP resources

processes.name: create-subnet
processes.description: Creates a subnetwork for the chosen region (NB - chose region and zone in the Configurations code).

processes.name: create-ssh-firewall-rule
processes.description: Creates the rule which allows SSH inbound from the public IP set in the Code (the "sshIngress" variable, hard coded to the "IAP TCP forwarding" subnet).

processes.name: create-wordpress-instance
processes.description: Create Wordpress Compute Engine instance using the Bitnami Image (currently provided in the Configurations "wpImageProject and wpImageUrl" variables)

processes.name: slack-send-message
processes.description: Sends a Slack message to the channel set in the "slackChannel" variable in Configurations confirming EC2 has been created. (Ensure you have built an App and set the token value in the Vault).

processes.name: Enable Cloud Resource Manager
processes.description: Enable the Cloud Resource Manager API

processes.name: create-http-firewall-rule
processes.description: Creates the rule which allows HTTP inbound from the internet (0.0.0.0/0).

processes.name: create-https-firewall-rule
processes.description: Creates the rule which allows HTTPS inbound from the internet (0.0.0.0/0).

processes.name: Enable Cloud Runtime Configuration
processes.description: Enable the Cloud Runtime Configuration API

processes.name: Enable Cloud Deployment Manager V2
processes.description: Enable the Cloud Deployment Manager V2 API

processes.name: Enable Identity and Access Management
processes.description: Enable the Identity and Access Management API

processes.name: Pause 20 seconds
processes.description: Pause for 20 seconds to all APIs to enable

exportedPipeline.description: This pipeline will deploy a standalone Wordpress environment within Google Cloud Platform (GCP). It will enable the required APIs, build a new VPC and subnet within a GCP project, allocate a static IP, create firewall rules to control traffic in and out of the Wordpress instance, before finally sending a slack notification to indicate completion of the pipeline.
